						<p>Damaged. The <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> of 79 <hi rend="italic">Nāḍus</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Nagarams</hi> in Tagaḍai-nāḍu, Puṟamalai-nāḍu, and [Aṅga]ṇap-paṟṟu, remitted the tax <hi rend="italic">kaṅka-kāṇi</hi> on temples for the welfare of the king and Sōmaya Daṇṇākkar.</p>						

